- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the integration of cloud-based CRM systems with other business applications, which has implications for how businesses operate and interact with customers. This falls under the broader category of computers and society.
- cs.DB (Databases): The paper discusses the integration of CRM systems with other systems, which involves managing and processing large amounts of data. This falls under the category of databases.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the design and implementation of a high-integrated cloud-based CRM system, which involves software engineering principles and practices.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): While not directly related to the content of the paper, the topic of cloud computing and its impact on computational complexity could be relevant.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses the use of cloud computing technology to integrate CRM with other systems, which involves distributed computing and networking.
